        "Unclear if failed DB writes for delivery records are logged with sufficient context to replay"
      ]
    },
    "metrics": {
      "coverage": "Partial — counters and latency histogram exist but critical operational metrics are missing",
      "gaps": [
        "No queue depth metric — this is your leading indicator of backpressure problems",
        "No emails_retried_total counter — you need to distinguish 'worked first try' from 'worked after 3 retries' to catch SendGrid degradation early",
        "No DB operation latency or error metrics",
        "No metric for SendGrid rate-limit (429) responses specifically",
        "No in-flight request gauge — needed to detect connection pool exhaustion"
      ]
    },
    "tracing": {
      "coverage": "Unknown — request IDs exist in logs but no mention of distributed tracing (e.g., OpenTelemetry spans across queue consume → SendGrid call → DB write)",
      "gaps": [
        "No trace correlation from queue message to final delivery outcome",
        "Cannot trace a single email's journey end-to-end through the system"
      ]
    },
    "debugging_capability": "Moderate. Structured JSON logging with request ID, duration, status code, and error details is a solid foundation. However, missing retry-level logging and no distributed tracing means debugging intermittent failures under load will require log correlation by timestamp, which is error-prone."
  },

  "resilience_assessment": {
    "failure_modes": [
      {
        "scenario": "SendGrid sustained outage (all requests fail for 10+ minutes)",
        "handling": "partial",
        "recommendation": "Add a circuit breaker (e.g., 50% error rate over 30s window → open for 60s). Without it, every request burns 30s (3 retries × 10s) before failing. At 100 req/s that's 3000 in-flight requests consuming threads/memory. Circuit breaker fails fast and gives SendGrid breathing room."
      },
      {
        "scenario": "SendGrid rate-limiting (429 responses)",
        "handling": "unhandled",
        "recommendation": "429s should not count as retryable the same way as 500s. Implement rate-limit-aware backoff using the Retry-After header from SendGrid. Without this, retries will worsen the rate-limiting."
